<TITLE> School Rugby begins Tuesday in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 25 (bdnews24.com)  The School Rugby Tournament, organised by the Bangladesh Rugby Association (BRA) and sponsored by Diamond Melamine Ltd, begins Tuesday at the Outer Stadium adjacent to Bangabandhu National Stadium. A total of eight teams, split into two groups, will play the robin-round matches and top two teams from each group will advance to the semifinals, BRA general secretary Mousum Ali said at a press conference Monday. He said that they conducted a training programme for 12 city schools, and ,of them ,eight schools were taking part in the tournament as they were forced to cut down the number of participants because of lack of balls and money. Of the estimated budget of Tk 1.64 lakh, the sponsor is providing Tk 1.10 lakh, said Ali. Tournament committee's vice president Monir Hossain and Diamond Melamine Ltd managing director Mokter Hossain were among others present. The participating teams are Nawabpur Govt. High School, Narinda Govt. High School, Islambagh Ashraf Ali High School, Heart to Reach School, Saint Gregory's School, West & High School, Hammadia High School and Rahmatullah Model High School. 
